<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8293&amp;p=86198#p86198"><![CDATA[
I threw together a little demo to try out the RGB fade: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://thefox.aspekt.fi/palette-fade.nes">http://thefox.aspekt.fi/palette-fade.nes</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Press A to do the usual "subtract $10 fade". Press B to do an RGB-fade. Hold down START while pressing either button to add the 3 additional tint steps in the beginning.<br /><br />As to which one looks better, it's largely subjective, although using the tint bits definitely adds a lot of smoothness. I doubt an Average Joe would notice any difference...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Sat Nov 12, 2011 3:06 am</p><hr />
