<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2011-11-10T11:07:00-07:00</updated>
<published>2011-11-10T11:07:00-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8293&amp;p=86124#p86124</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8293&amp;p=86124#p86124"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Fade in, fade out]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8293&amp;p=86124#p86124"><![CDATA[
I just subtract $10 every frame and apply three special cases: $F0-&gt;$02 (dark gray into dark blue), $80-$FF-&gt;$0F (colors that have reached black), and $0D-&gt;$0F (to protect sync integrity). This also allows a distinction in the palette between $20, which is ordinary white, and $30, which shows up as superbright white during fades.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Nov 10, 2011 11:07 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
